FBIS4-37640 "drnes121_s_94002" FBIS-NES-94-121 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 Iran Besharati Claims Suspects Arrested Besharati Claims Suspects Arrested LD2306111094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 23 Jun 94 LD2306111094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] In an exclusive interview with our correspondent today Interior Minister Besharati divulged more information on the recent bomb explosion by the terrorist group, the hypocrites [monafeqin -- reference to Mojahedin-e Khalq], at Imam Reza's shrine. Referring to the fact that the number of martyrs in the incident was 24, the Interior Minister said: Nine of the martyrs were from Mashhad and 15 were from other towns. He said the amount of explosives used was 10 lb, about 4.5 kg, of the C-4 variety. He added: The bomb's timer was set for 10 minutes. He added: Thus far a number of suspects have been arrested in this connection.
